   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary74.jpg"/>
            <dateline><date when="1862-06-03">Tuesday 3</date>.</dateline>
            <p>We went to <placeName type="Town" cert="medium" key="Washington N.C"
                  ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl090"
                     >town</placeName>. We have a
                  <objectName type="vehicle">boat</objectName> and boats crew, and it is a pleasant
               ride down. We were fortunate in going today, by being enabled to see the review of
               the <orgName role="Military" type="Division">1st division</orgName>. It was really
               splendid, the <orgName role="soldiers" type="Pioneers">pioneers</orgName> had
                  <objectName type="clothing">leather or linen aprons</objectName> - the long train
               of <objectName type="equipment">artillery</objectName>, the savage, devilish looking
                  <objectName type="equipment">marine battery</objectName>, drawn by <orgName
                  type="Sailors">sailors</orgName> &amp; <orgName role="Combat Branch"
                  type="Cavalry">the cavalry</orgName>.</p>
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary75.jpg"/>
            <p>Made a spectacle such as I have never yet witnessed. In display it far exceeded ours
               - they are all <orgName role="military" type="union">Yankee regiments -
                  Massachusetts</orgName>. This
               then you know, they call us the fighting division.
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
